a new literary history of the Anthropocene in a period before it was named.These close readings show the entanglement of the human and the lithic in periods well before the geological turn of contemporary cultural studies. In those depictions of human-mineral encounters, the minerality of the human and the minerality of the imagination become apparent. In registering libidinal investments in the lithosphere that extend beyond Carboniferous deposits and beyond any carbon imaginary, The Geological Unconscious points toward alternative relations with, and less destructive mobilizations of, the geologic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEcology in literature. 0aGeology in literature. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aAnthropocene.  aClimate Fiction.  aDeep time.  aEcocriticism.  aEcopoetics.  aGeopoetics.  aLiterary Criticism.  aRealism.  aRomanticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311072271008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP/FUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311070632140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823288120zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823288120423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823288120.jpg  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 202